          "question": "I traveled through an international airport. Do I need to notify the Health Department?",
          "answer": "\n\nTravelers with international layovers returning to Vermont need to follow the same monitoring guidelines as if they are a returning traveler from that country. If you have a layover in **China** or **Iran**, you should:\n\n1. Call your health care provider and\n\n2. Call the Vermont Department of Health at 802-863-7240\n\nRead the CDC’s guidance on [returning from international travel](https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/travelers/after-travel-precautions.html).",
