      "id": 4565,
      "revisions": [
        {
          "id": 4565,
          "question": "Where is it safe to travel internationally? Is it safe to go on a cruise ship or river cruise?",
          "answer": "\n\nThe Department of State has issued a [Global Level 4 Health Advisory](https://travel.state.gov/content/travel/en/traveladvisories/ea/travel-advisory-alert-global-level-4-health-advisory-issue.html), and the CDC recommends that travelers avoid all nonessential international travel.\n\nThe CDC also recommends that no one travel on cruise ships, including river cruises, worldwide. That’s because the risk of COVID-19 on cruise ships is high.\n\nStay up to date on the [latest COVID-19 travel advisories from the CDC](https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/travelers/index.html). \n\nYou can also check the [CDC's FAQs for Travelers](https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/travelers/faqs.html).",
          "date": "2020-07-21"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 4566,
      "revisions": [
        {
          "id": 4566,
          "question": "What should I do if I have traveled internationally or traveled by cruise ship?",
          "answer": "\n\nIf you’ve returned from international travel or from a cruise ship or river cruise voyage, you should for quarantine for 14 days.\n\nCheck the Health Department’s webpage for [what to do if you are visiting or returning to Vermont](https://www.healthvermont.gov/response/coronavirus-covid-19/traveling-vermont). Get the latest travel and quarantine guidance, sign up to get daily symptom check reminders by email, text or phone, learn about testing options during quarantine, and find out how to safely connect with friends and family.\n\nFind more information from the CDC about [returning from international travel](https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/travelers/after-travel-precautions.html) and [returning from cruise ship and river cruise voyages](https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/travelers/returning-cruise-voyages.html).\n\nIf you develop [symptoms of COVID-19](https://www.healthvermont.gov/response/coronavirus-covid-19/about-coronavirus-disease-covid-19), contact your health care provider right away.\n\nStay up to date on the [latest COVID-19 travel advisories from the CDC](https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/travelers/).",
          "date": "2020-07-21"
        }
