          "question": "What is Vermont doing?",
          "answer": "\n\nOn July 14, Governor Phil Scott extended Vermont’s State of Emergency through August 15 to help ensure Vermont has all the necessary resources to respond to this evolving public health emergency. Find details on all [executive orders](https://governor.vermont.gov/document-types/executive-orders).\n\nThe strategies continue to be updated based on guidance from federal and state public health officials. Find a [summary of current strategies on the Governor's website](https://governor.vermont.gov/covid19response).",
