          "id": 4590,
          "question": "Why is Vermont reporting people who have tested for COVID-19 in the way that it is?",
          "answer": "\n\nWith the quickly changing situation, we continue to adjust reporting, looking for the best ways to communicate with the public. Information is updated daily on the on [Current Activity in Vermont data dashboard](https://www.healthvermont.gov/COVID19-currentactivity).\n\nA [Weekly Summary of Vermont COVID-19 Data](https://www.healthvermont.gov/sites/default/files/documents/pdf/Weekly-Summary-of-Data.pdf) is also available that includes more details on who has been impacted by COVID-19 in Vermont. You can find out more about testing trends, outbreaks, pre-existing conditions and symptoms of Vermonters with COVID-19.\n\nWe need to assume that we are all at risk of infection and follow these general precautions: wear a cloth face mask or covering, keep a 6-foot distance from others, wash your hands often, and stay home if you are sick.",
