      "revisions": [
        {
          "id": 4591,
          "question": "Are mass gatherings (ceremonies, events, fairs or festivals) allowed?",
          "answer": "\n\nEvent venues can hold events, such as weddings, funerals, parties, concerts and large sporting events with certain occupancy limits and health and safety precautions. Outdoor services, events and gatherings are strongly preferred. Find up-to-date information on the [number of people allowed in event venues](https://accd.vermont.gov/news/update-new-work-safe-additions-stay-home-stay-safe-order#event-venues) from the Agency of Commerce and Community Development.\n\nAll traditional fairs and festivals have been canceled until further notice.\n\nOrganized outdoor markets, like flea markets, must follow the [farmers market guidance](https://agriculture.vermont.gov/agency-agriculture-food-markets-news/farmers-market-guidance-updated) from the Agency of Agriculture, Food & Markets (AAFM).\n\n[Farmers markets](https://accd.vermont.gov/news/update-new-work-safe-additions-be-smart-stay-safe-order#farmers-markets) and [pick-your-own farms and orchards](https://accd.vermont.gov/news/update-new-work-safe-additions-be-smart-stay-safe-order#retail-operations) must follow best practices outlined by AAFM.\n\nLibraries, galleries, museums, theaters and other [indoor arts, culture and entertainment organizations](https://accd.vermont.gov/news/update-new-work-safe-additions-be-smart-stay-safe-order#indoor-arts-culture-and-entertainment) are open with certain occupancy limits and health and safety precautions.\n\nFind more information on the health and safety requirements for [sectors that are open](https://accd.vermont.gov/news/update-new-work-safe-additions-stay-home-stay-safe-order) from the Agency of Commerce and Community Development (ACCD).\n\nAt any gathering or event, everyone should follow these general precautions: wear a cloth face mask or covering, keep a 6-foot distance from others, wash their hands often, and stay home if they are sick.",
          "date": "2020-07-21"
