        {
          "id": 4595,
          "question": "What should I do if I’m being monitored by the Health Department and then become sick?",
          "answer": "\n\nIf you have developed [symptoms of COVID-19](https://www.healthvermont.gov/response/coronavirus-covid-19/about-coronavirus-disease-covid-19) **AND**\n\nHave returned from **China** or **Iran**, or are a **close contact** of a person who tested positive for COVID-19, you should:\n\n1.  Call your health care provider and\n2.  Call the Vermont Department of Health at 802-863-7240.\n\nIf you are being monitored because you have returned from an affected area other than China or Iran, or by cruise ship, you should call your health care provider if you become sick. If you are enrolled in Sara Alert, report your symptoms to Sara Alert, and follow the steps given. It is not necessary to call the Health Department to report symptoms.",
