      "id": 4597,
      "revisions": [
        {
          "id": 4597,
          "question": "Do homemade cloth face masks or coverings work?",
          "answer": "\n\nAs the state continues to reopen, it is important to make wearing cloth face masks or coverings a habit and to bring one with you whenever you leave home. Cloth face masks or coverings need to be worn in public settings when you cannot keep a 6-foot distance from others, for example, visiting a grocery store or on a crowded sidewalk or bike path.\n\nWearing a homemade cloth face mask or covering can offer some protection to others. This is because the virus can spread even if a person does not have any symptoms. The cloth face mask or covering can contain respiratory droplets and prevent them from spreading to others.\n\nWhile health care workers may be able to use homemade cloth face masks or coverings as a last resort, medical-grade masks are considered personal protective equipment. These should be reserved for health care workers.\n\nLearn more about [using cloth face masks or coverings to help slow the spread of COVID-19](https://www.healthvermont.gov/sites/default/files/documents/pdf/COVID-19-VDH-mask-guidance.pdf).",
          "date": "2020-07-21"
