      "id": 4605,
      "revisions": [
        {
          "id": 4605,
          "question": "What should health care workers do?",
          "answer": "\n\nThe Health Department now has a dedicated webpage for health care workers - healthvermont.gov/covid19-providers. It includes current guidance, health alerts, and resources for protecting patients and health care workers in different settings.\n\nReport all suspected cases of COVID-19 immediately to the Vermont Department of Health Infectious Disease Epidemiology by calling 802-863-7240 (24/7).\n\nIf you suspect that a patient with a fever or respiratory illness has COVID-19:\n\n*   Give the patient a surgical mask.\n*   Notify facility infection control personnel immediately.\n*   Use standard precautions, contact precautions, airborne precautions, and use eye protection when entering the room.\n*   Evaluate the patient in a private room with the door closed, ideally in an airborne infection isolation room\n\nHealth care providers are encouraged to order a test for any child or adult who is showing symptoms of COVID-19, even if their symptoms are mild. If an asymptomatic patient who is currently in quarantine would like to end their quarantine on Day 7 or later based upon a negative test result, health care providers can test them in their office or refer them to a pop-up testing site.",
          "date": "2020-07-21"
