          "id": 4630,
          "question": "What should businesses and non-profits do?",
          "answer": "\n\nVermont is starting a phased approach to reopen the economy, balancing overall social and economic wellbeing with preventing a rise in COVID-19 that would set us back. Businesses deemed “essential” may continue to operate under pre-existing\n guidance, with the addition of the [mandatory health and safety \nrequirements](https://accd.vermont.gov/news/update-new-work-safe-additions-stay-home-stay-safe-order). \n\nThe Agency of Commerce and Community Development (ACCD) has the resources businesses need on their [COVID-19 Recovery Resource Center for Businesses](https://accd.vermont.gov/covid-19/business):\n\n* A step-by-step [reopening guide for businesses](https://accd.vermont.gov/covid-19/business/restart)\n\n* Up-to-date [sector-specific guidance](https://accd.vermont.gov/content/stay-home-stay-safe-sector-specific-guidance)\n\n* Mandatory [health and safety requirements](https://accd.vermont.gov/news/update-new-work-safe-additions-be-smart-stay-safe-order). This includes having a [health safety officer onsite at every shift](https://accd.vermont.gov/covid-19/business/stay-home-stay-safe-business-faqs#does-my-business-need-to-hire-a-new-health-safety-officer) and requiring employees to wear face coverings over their nose and mouth when in the presence of others. Businesses and non-profits may require customers or clients to wear masks.\n\n* Answers to [Be Smart, Stay Safe FAQs for Businesses](https://accd.vermont.gov/covid-19-guidance/stay-home-stay-safe-business-faqs)\n\nFind more [health resources for businesses](https://www.healthvermont.gov/response/coronavirus-covid-19/communities-and-workplaces) and read the [Health & Safety Tips for Essential Businesses](https://www.healthvermont.gov/sites/default/files/documents/pdf/COVID19-Essential-Workers-Health-Safety-Tips.pdf) from the Health Department.\n\nThe ACCD wants to hear from all Vermont businesses impacted by the response to the COVID-19 virus. Please share your experiences on the [AC