      "revisions": [
        {
          "id": 4647,
          "question": "Is there a rapid (fast) test for COVID-19?",
          "answer": "\n\nVermont has a limited supply of rapid COVID-19 test machines and supplies. These tests take about 15 minutes for results. Currently, the Health Department is confirming the accuracy of these new tests to detect COVID-19 before they are used. Once they are validated, the Health Department will determine the best locations for these testing machines based on a number of factors. Potential locations could include hospitals, small facilities experiencing a COVID-19 outbreak, and new testing sites",
          "date": "2020-07-21"
        },
        {
          "id": 4647,
          "question": "Is there a rapid (fast) test for COVID-19?",
          "answer": "\n\nThere are a few different types of COVID-19 tests, and some are faster than others. The tests also look for different information. If you think you need to be tested for COVID-19, talk with your health care provider about what testing might be appropriate. If you do not have a health care provider, call 2-1-1 to be connected with a local [community or hospital-connected clinic](https://www.navigateresources.net/211vermont/Subcategory.aspx?;;0;;N;0;276976;Health%20Care,%20Dental%20Care). Get more information about the COVID-19 tests that are currently available from the [Food and Drug Administration](https://www.fda.gov/consumers/consumer-updates/coronavirus-testing-basics).",
          "date": "2020-07-24"
        }
