          "id": 4655,
          "question": "I tested positive for COVID-19 but I never had symptoms. When can I stop home isolation?",
          "answer": "\n\nIf you didn’t have symptoms when you were tested, you may stop home isolation when at least 10 days have passed since the date of your first positive COVID-19 test.\n\nAfter stopping home isolation, continue to stay 6 feet away from others and wear a [cloth face mask or covering](https://www.healthvermont.gov/sites/default/files/documents/pdf/COVID-19-VDH-mask-guidance.pdf) whenever other people are present.",
          "date": "2020-07-21"
        }
      ]
    },
