          "question": "What should businesses do to protect workers and customers?",
          "answer": "\n\nCurrent information is on the Agency of Commerce and Community Development’s (ACCD’s) [COVID-19 Recovery Resource Center for Businesses](https://accd.vermont.gov/covid-19/business/stay-home-stay-safe-business-faqs):\n\n*   Up-to-date [guidance and mandatory health and safety requirements](https://accd.vermont.gov/content/stay-home-stay-safe-sector-specific-guidance). This includes having a [health safety officer onsite at every shift](https://accd.vermont.gov/covid-19/business/stay-home-stay-safe-business-faqs#does-my-business-need-to-hire-a-new-health-safety-officer) and requiring employees to wear face coverings over their nose and mouth when in the presence of others. Businesses may require customers to wear cloth face masks or coverings.\n*   Answers to [Be Smart, Stay Safe FAQs for Businesses](https://accd.vermont.gov/covid-19-guidance/stay-home-stay-safe-business-faqs)\n\nMore resources are available from the Health Department:\n\n*   [Health resources for businesses and food and lodging businesses](https://www.healthvermont.gov/response/coronavirus-covid-19/communities-and-workplaces)\n*   [COVID-19 Health & Safety Tips for Essential Businesses](https://www.healthvermont.gov/sites/default/files/documents/pdf/COVID19-Essential-Workers-Health-Safety-Tips.pdf)\n*   [What to do if an Employee Tests Positive for COVID-19](https://www.healthvermont.gov/sites/default/files/documents/pdf/COVID-19-What-employers-should-do-if-their-employee-tests-positive.pdf)\n*   [COVID-19 Guidance for Food and Lodging Businesses](https://www.healthvermont.gov/sites/default/files/documents/pdf/EH-COVID-19-Food-Lodging-Business-Fact-Sheet.pdf) and [Best Practices for Retail Food Stores, Restaurants, and Food Pick-Up/Delivery Services During the COVID-19 Pandemic](https://www.fda.gov/food/food-safety-during-emergencies/best-practices-retail-food-stores-restaurants-and-food-pick-updelivery-services-during-covid-19) from the FDA.\n\nThe ACCD wants to hear from al