          "question": "Can I buy or sign a long-term lease (more than 30 days) for a new apartment or house?",
          "answer": "\n\nLong-term rental leases are allowed. Moving and moving services are also allowed, as long as people keep a 6-foot distance from each other. Wearing cloth face masks and coverings is recommended. More housing information is available at the Agency of Commerce and Community Development's (ACCD’s) [COVID-19 Resource Recovery Center](http://accd.vermont.gov/covid-19/individuals#individual-housing).\n\nReal estate services, including real estate firms, brokerages, attorneys or individuals, must work remotely as much as possible to minimize in-person contact. Real estate and related services (such as title searches, appraisals, and home inspections) are operating under certain health and safety requirements including keeping at least 6 feet away from others and wearing cloth face masks or coverings. \n\nOut-of-state buyers and renters must follow all quarantine requirements.\n\nFind details and up-to-date [information on real estate](https://accd.vermont.gov/content/stay-home-stay-safe-sector-specific-guidance#real-estate) from the ACCD.",
