          "answer": "\n\nVermont has begun a phased approach to reopen the economy, balancing overall social and economic wellbeing with preventing a rise in COVID-19 that would set us back.\n\nCurrent information for [businesses, non-profit and government operations that are open](https://accd.vermont.gov/news/update-new-work-safe-additions-be-smart-stay-safe-order) and their health and safety requirements under the Be Smart, Stay Safe Order is available from the Agency of Commerce and Community Development (ACCD).\n\nBusinesses can find a [step-by-step guide to reopening](https://accd.vermont.gov/covid-19/business/restart) and up-to-date [sector-specific guidance](https://accd.vermont.gov/content/stay-home-stay-safe-sector-specific-guidance) from the ACCD.\n\nFind the most recent [Governor’s Executive Orders](https://governor.vermont.gov/document-types/executive-orders) for more information.",
