        {
          "id": 4695,
          "question": "Are outpatient services open?",
          "answer": "\n\nOutpatient services are reopened for professions licensed by the [Office of Professional Regulation](https://sos.vermont.gov/opr/).\n\nThose professions that provide care without physical contact or with some physical contact  may resume outpatient services – such as licensed alcohol and drug counselors (LADACs), Allied Mental Health, dieticians, psychologists, social workers, acupuncturists, chiropractors, physical therapists, occupational therapists, opticians and optometrists.\n\nFor those professions involved in care that is more likely to expose them to the COVID-19 virus – such as doctors of osteopathy, naturopathy, physician assistants, and nurses – outpatient clinic visits and diagnostic imaging may resume.",
          "date": "2020-07-21"
        }
      ]
