          "question": "Do I need to quarantine if I do a short trip (day trip)?",
          "answer": "\n\nPeople who live near the Vermont border and regularly travel to and from a neighboring state may make day trips to Vermont for work, health care, and other essential needs like groceries or visitation for parental shared custody without quarantining. \n\nIf you go on a day trip that is **not** in an [approved county with low rates of active cases](https://accd.vermont.gov/covid-19/restart/cross-state-travel), you must quarantine in Vermont upon return.",
