          "question": "Are there any travel restrictions if I am traveling through Vermont?",
          "answer": "\n\nIf you are only traveling through and not staying in Vermont (for example, driving through Vermont to another state, flying to Vermont and immediately picking up a rental car to drive to another state), there are no quarantine or other restrictions you need to follow. If you need to make stops in Vermont or are otherwise not in a vehicle while you are traveling through Vermont, please follow these general precautions to help prevent the spread of the virus: wear a cloth face mask or covering, keep a 6-foot distance from others, and wash your hands often.",
